<h2>Understand reporting requirements</h2>

<p>Understanding when and why you need to submit performance metrics helps ensure compliance and accurate reporting.</p>

<h3>When is reporting required?</h3>
<p>Reporting requirements are determined by:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Business area configuration:</strong> Your business area may have specific reporting periods</li>
    <li><strong>Period exclusions:</strong> Some periods may be excluded from reporting</li>
    <li><strong>Product exclusions:</strong> Your product may be excluded for specific periods</li>
    <li><strong>Reporting hierarchy:</strong> Parent products may determine requirements</li>
</ul>

<h3>Checking if you need to report</h3>
<p>To check if reporting is required:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Go to <strong>Reporting → Operational reporting</strong></li>
    <li>Look for your product in the list</li>
    <li>If your product appears, reporting is required</li>
    <li>If it doesn't appear, check:
        <ul>
            <li>Is the period excluded?</li>
            <li>Is your business area excluded?</li>
            <li>Is your product excluded?</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h3>Due dates</h3>
<p>Metrics are typically due by:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Default:</strong> 3rd working day of the following month</li>
    <li><strong>Overrides:</strong> Administrators can set custom due dates</li>
    <li><strong>Status indicators:</strong> The system shows upcoming, due, late, or submitted</li>
</ul>

<h3>Reporting status</h3>
<p>Your product's reporting status shows:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Upcoming:</strong> Period hasn't ended yet</li>
    <li><strong>Due:</strong> Period has ended, submission is due</li>
    <li><strong>Late:</strong> Past the due date, not yet submitted</li>
    <li><strong>Submitted:</strong> Metrics have been submitted</li>
</ul>

<h3>Business area configurations</h3>
<p>Business areas can have:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Specific reporting periods (from/until dates)</li>
    <li>Overrides for period exclusions</li>
    <li>Custom reporting requirements</li>
</ul>
<p>Check with your business area administrator if you're unsure about requirements.</p>

<h3>Period exclusions</h3>
<p>Periods may be excluded from reporting for:</p>
<ul>
    <li>System migrations</li>
    <li>Holiday periods</li>
    <li>Organisational changes</li>
    <li>Other operational reasons</li>
</ul>
<p>Business area configurations can override period exclusions.</p>

<h3>Product exclusions</h3>
<p>Individual products can be excluded from reporting for specific periods if:</p>
<ul>
    <li>The product is being retired</li>
    <li>There are data quality issues</li>
    <li>Special circumstances apply</li>
</ul>
<p>Product exclusions are managed by administrators.</p>

<h3>Getting help</h3>
<p>If you're unsure about reporting requirements:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Check the product list - if it appears, reporting is required</li>
    <li>Contact your business area administrator</li>
    <li>Review the product history to see past reporting patterns</li>
    <li>Check admin settings if you have admin access</li>
</ul>

<h3>Compliance</h3>
<p>Submitting metrics on time:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Ensures accurate operational reporting</li>
    <li>Helps with portfolio management</li>
    <li>Supports decision-making</li>
    <li>Maintains compliance with reporting requirements</li>
</ul>

